data.title: Liza Morberg: Movies, TV, and Bio

data.text:
Liza Morberg is an internationally acclaimed director and writer. Born and raised in Stockholm, Sweden, Liza has a diverse background in acting, dance, DJ-ing, and photography. She honed her skills further at the prestigious USC Film School in Los Angeles.

Liza's impressive body of work includes music videos for Mapei and Robin Schulz, the latter accumulating over 230 million views. She also has an extensive commercial reel, having worked with top agencies such as Forsman Bodenfors, DDB, and brands like H&M, Coca Cola, and Volvo.

Liza's debut coming-of-age film, "Alone Together," won Best International Feature in America, and her thriller TV series, "The Chosen One," directed for Swedish Television, was sold internationally. She also wrote, directed, and produced the critically acclaimed film "Sensory Overload" for SVT.

With her unique perspective, Liza remains dedicated to honing her craft and striving to create meaningful stories through her work.
